comment.body:
@tkarita, yea, I've seen some attempts at hosting 1 vid per site. It's very clunky, and ZeroNet doesn't lend itself to distributing large files very well.

@quadrangle, now that we have merger sites, we can pretty much reproduce reddit. Each hub would be a subreddit, and then the merger site would be like the main reddit page.

Torrents are pretty much done. I think people are waiting on the KAT clone now and we're all good to go. And yea, a community is definitely needed. Which is why I think ZeroMe has been such a success.
